This involves analyzing users' interactions and using them as sensors to estimate current incidence. This falls under the scope of social and information networks. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a framework for enhancing epidemiological models for dengue fever. This involves developing software to collect and analyze Twitter data, as well as integrating this data with traditional epidemiological models. This falls under the scope of software engineering. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences): The paper explores the use of social media data (specifically Twitter) to monitor and predict the incidence of dengue fever. This involves analyzing users' interactions and behavior, as well as understanding the social dynamics of the disease. This falls under the scope of social and behavioral sciences. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper involves collecting and analyzing large amounts of data from Twitter to estimate the current incidence of dengue fever.
